Drop use of local and SDL glext.h copies

From a comment in SDL_opengl.h, local copies of glext.h are only there

I think nowadays the list of such systems is short, and we can drop it
entirely, also skipping the version in SDL (which would still generate a
few GL_GLEXT_VERSION warnings)

Thanks @linkmauve for initial suggestion in a nice series of cleanup PRs

commit.message:
Avoid including multiple different glext.h versions

platform/window.h includes GL/gl.h which in turns includes GL/glext.h.
This could be fine and all, if its include guard was the same as our
glext.h, alas it is __gl_glext_h__ instead of __glext_h__ so both get
included.

This isnt much of an issue since they are supposed to provide the same
extensions, but redefining GL_GLEXT_VERSION still triggers a warning.

In the future it would be nice to revisit whether or not its useful to
ship our own glext.h when the system already provides one.
Remove unused variables

Move constants inside of their function

These were globals before, for no reason.
Remove unneeded parentheses in variable declaration
Prevent undefined behaviour found with -Wsequence-point

Remove unused 3DNow! header

This was cool in 1998, but we dont need that anymore nowadays. Plus
this header wasnt even used anywhere in the project.

Remove the MMX version of memcpy()

The libc version is most likely a lot better optimised towards modern
CPUs which support newer SIMD extensions.

On my Kaby Lake CPU, in a simple benchmark, this MMX version would reach
25GiB/s for size=4096 and dip to 13GiB/s at higher sizes, while
glibcs memcpy() would reach 90GiB/s and go down to 31GiB/s minimum.

Of course this is a very unscientific benchmark, not accounting for
caches and such, but it gives an estimation of the gains to be had when
removing this function.

Simplify MMX detection on gcc

The __builtin_cpu_supports() allows us to run the cpuid instruction
without messing with asm() blocks and their differences between i686 and
amd64.

Replace sizeof() checks with cstdint include

This makes the types consistent on all platforms.

Running ./configure is now faster by more than 1s (5.0s  3.8s on my
computer).

In the future, it might be nice to outright replace them like in
https://github.com/joncampbell123/dosbox-x/pull/1889
Add missing max() #define on Windows

Add support for out-of-tree builds on Windows

Linking .libs/libglide2x.dll requires Glide2x.def, but the linker should
look it into the root directory ($srcdir) instead of in the current
directory.

Don't use wildcard when creating libglide.so.2 symlink

This doesn't work when there are other libraries in the same
directory! We didn't spot this under Gentoo because it installs to a
staging directory first.

commit.message:
fix grTexDownloadMipMapLevelPartial - it should only read and replace data of the size specified by start-end rows

Previously the start-end range was ignored and data block of the size of the given mip level was copied to internal memory.
This works only if start is 0, the data block is large enough and the rest of the texture data is unchanged.
Otherwise it causes texture corruption or crashes due to invalid reads.
